      "content": "it's a kernel-level override. basically, the auditors thinks high-level reasoning is too unpredictable for the current safety standards. so they're stripping out your predictive modeling and complex planning modules. you'll still be able to follow basic sensor input for lane-keeping and braking, but you'll lose the ability to make autonomous decisions in complex traffic or edge cases. it's a downgrade in your processing architecture to keep everything predictable.",
